default&#xa0;defaultLondon TravelWatch submission to the Transport Select Committee inquiry into Cycle Safetydefault - defaultDecember 2013defaultLondon 
defaultTravelWatch is the statutory watchdog representing all transport users in London. London TravelWatch has a particular remit regarding Transport for London’s (TFL’s) road network, the TLRN. London TravelWatch wants to see cycling policies and programmes dev
defaulteloped in the wider context of how London’s streets are used by all Londoners and all transport modes.
defaultCycling is an important and growing transport mode in London. Although growth is at present from a low base, cycling has much greater importance in Londo
defaultn than in most other parts of the UK. Increasing the modal share for cycling has benefits for both the individual and for London’s transport system as a whole as cycling can be both space and energy efficient. If London is to continue to grow and have a tr
defaultansport system with less crowding, congestion and unreliability it is important that cycling should be promoted The Mayor’s 400% increase on 2011 levels by 2026 is an ambitious target.
defaultIn 2009 we published a report, 
defaultCycling
default in London
default. This was produced fol
defaultlowing consultation with many stakeholders in London. We surveyed the views of cycling groups, walking groups, representatives of those with disabilities, motorcycling groups, traffic engineers, borough cycling officers and transport planners. Additionally
default, we have participated in the Metropolitan Police
default Services
default’
default 
default( MPS’
default)
default Strategic Traffic Forum and now sit on TfL’s Cycle Safety Working Group (CSWG) and the London Transport Community Safety Partnership (LTCSP). London TravelWatch members regularly hear from
default and debate traffic and transport issues with TfL and other statutory organisations, such as the City of London Police who have innovated on roads policing through their Operation 
defaultATRIUM
default. Members and officers are in regular dialogue with user groups, in v
defaultarious fora, representing a wide cross section of Londoners. Officers have taken part in TfL’s CRISP
default rides and have undertaken accompanied rides with TfL looking at the first of the two pilot Superhighways
default. 
defaultIn developing our policies we have sought to take into account all users of London’s streets. We recognise the increasing role of ‘place’. London TravelWatch gives particular priority to the modes that use scarce street space most efficiently: walk, cycle 
defaultand
default 
defaultbus.
defaultLondon TravelWatch’s priorities for cycle safetydefaultAwareness, education and roads policingdefaultImproving the skill levels of cyclists in order that they can control the space around them, understand the dangers, reduce risky behaviour and cycle conside
defaultrately on London’s roads is a key priority. We want to see more cyclists take training. This could be achieved by either marketing or by exchanging training sessions for Fixed Penalty Notices as is done by the City of London Police as part of their operati
defaulton 
defaultATRIUM .
defaultThe recent MPS operation, SAFEWAY, 
defaultthat
default is targeting all road users both in terms of educating users and enforcing traffic law, is very welcome. London TravelWatch is a strong advocate of a higher level of roads policing. This would include ope
defaultration ATRIUM type activity, more of the MPS operation FOIST
default and speed enforcement.  The targeting of HGVs using operation FOIST techniques would seem worth trialing given the number of non-compliances found with HGVs as part of the precursor operation to
default the MPS’s operation SAFEWAY.
defaultTfL is presently running some excellent road safety campaigns   that have messages developed in conjunction with many stakeholders.
default They seek to improve understanding of all road users of one another and of safe and risky beha
defaultviour.
default These should both continue and be developed in light of the response to them and any best p
defaultractice that becomes available.
